<br>
This raid is limited to lvl 45+ and may also be limited in the numbers of people who will be allowed to attend. Please note that a base CR of 70 and MR of 50 is MANDATORY for this raid. If you do not have equipment to put your CR and MR at these levels then please do not ask to participate unless you are either a bard or an enchanter.<br>
<br>
Loot rules are as follows :-<br>
<br>
With the following exceptions, all items may be rolled for only if usable by your class<br>
Loot rules are as follows :-<br>
<br>
I WILL be reserving a white dragon scale for my epic if one drops.  If I do so I will be removing myself from all other rolls automatically.<br>
Only casters classes (ENC, MAG, NEC, WIZ, SHM, CLR, DRU) may roll on the eyepatch<br>
Only melee classes (WAR, PAL, ROG, MNK, RNG, BRD, SHD)  classes may roll on the belt <br>
Only Rogues may roll for the spear<br>
Only Bards may roll for the White Dragon Scale<br>
Only Monks may roll on the bag<br>
You may roll for ONE item and ONE item only<br>
<br>
I have thought long and hard about what to do in cases of multiple drops of the same item.  My decision is that there will be no change to the previous method.  Therefore if two items of the same type drop only those who are eligible will be allowed to roll on the second item and may roll even if they have rolled on the first item as long as they have not won anything.<br>
<br>
As an addendum, if three items of the same type drop the third item will be lottoed as a free roll.  This will mean that all non-winners on the first two items may roll but so can all those who were not eligible to roll for anything else.  This is a rare occurence but has happened in the past (3 staves of the Heirophant from Naggy a few weeks back).<br>
<br>
Rally point will be the King Room in Permafrost<br>
<br>
All participants are expected to be at the Permafrost king room by 5:00PM PST. Please try to arrive earlier if at all possible. The raid will commence no later than 5:30PM PST.  You will need to notify me in advance if you wish to attend so that I can begin to form groups prior to everyone's arrival.<br>
<br>
I look forward to seeing you all.  Lets make it a good one!<br>
